## PR Workflow

Every change follows this flow — whether driven by a human or an AI agent:

| Step | Who | What |
|------|-----|------|
| 1. Plan | Human or Planner agent | Create/select an exec-plan in `docs/exec-plans/active/` |
| 2. Implement | Implementer agent | Write code following layer rules, referencing the exec-plan |
| 3. Self-check | Implementer agent | Run build + test + lint locally before committing |
| 4. Open PR | Implementer agent (or human) | Push branch, open PR with exec-plan link in description |
| 5. Review loop | Arch → Security → Reviewer | Each reviewer agent checks their domain; ANY fail → back to step 2 |
| 6. CI gate | Automated | `harnesskit enforce` + `harnesskit doctor` must pass in CI |
| 7. Merge | Human | A human reviews and merges — per OpenAI: "users must manually review and validate all agent-generated code" |
| 8. Post-merge | Doc-Gardener agent | Updates QUALITY_SCORE.md, checks doc links |

> **Rule**: Agents propose changes and open PRs. Humans review, approve, and merge (per [OpenAI Codex guidance](https://openai.com/index/introducing-codex/): "users must manually review and validate all agent-generated code before integration").

